NHL ENTRY DRAFT
June 24, 2000
Rostislav Klesla
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT







Q. Congratulations on being drafted. How does it feel to be the first pick of the
Columbus Blue Jackets?

ROSTISLAV KLESLA: It feels good, you know. They're a special team. It feels good.

Q. Describe what kind of game you play for people who haven't seen you?

ROSTISLAV KLESLA: I'm a defense. I like to play...(Inaudible). I like the physical
stuff, too, but I like to score goals.

Q. Are you looking to make this team in September?

ROSTISLAV KLESLA: Well, I don't know. I'll do my best for being there, and then the
coaches and general manager will decide if it's me. They know I'm ready for the team next
season.

